Not much. <g>

the left.

Thanks to those of you who knew how to look that up!

Sandra

Hey!

Found *Mayotte* in the Washington Post website!

Go Holly!

Kelli~

SandraDodd@... wrote:
I hope this doesn't take a whole day to arrive like some of yesterdays'
e-mails did!

Holly really wants to see what happens when you win ten rounds of Hangaroo,
and we have nine, but the #10 we can't get. It's capitals of countries, but
this country isn't in a 2004 almanac, so I'm guessing it's either a protectorate
or a colony, or it's changed its name or existed a few years ago when this
version of Hangaroo came out, but no more.

We have this, and it's been sitting on the desktop since yesterday:

MAMO _ _ _ O _,
MA _ O _ _ E

I hope someone here knows it or maybe has a crossword kind of search. My
browser is fritzed, and Kirby was gone four days so his computer's not mine
anymore (and he's asleep in there).

Sandra
